                            <comment id="15155003" author="daijy" created="Fri, 19 Feb 2016 22:28:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It might be hard to come out a test cuz the reproduction involve namenode HA setting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15155159" author="rohini" created="Fri, 19 Feb 2016 23:49:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;UDFContext.getUDFContext().getJobConf() is usually null on the frontend. How does it work when schema is parsed in the front-end?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15155162" author="daijy" created="Fri, 19 Feb 2016 23:51:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Frontend still using new Configuration(), which is the same as before. The issue happens in the backend.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15155183" author="rohini" created="Sat, 20 Feb 2016 00:02:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Got it. new Configuration() will load the defaults in the frontend and that will include hdfs-site.xml.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15155225" author="daijy" created="Sat, 20 Feb 2016 00:40:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk. Thanks Rohini for review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
